<br>
At Olympus the hall Poseidon picked to have his feast is set and the last remnants of decoration and the preparation of food and drink are being finished. The sea god leaves his palace and as the doors slam shut behind him the god turns and looks at his home. He smiles and walks off to the stables where he boards the golden chariot. The servants fix his atire and then Poseidon orders the mares to be off. The chariot jerks and shoots out of the stables and pass crowds of animals and immortals and nymphs and many other creatures of his kingdom who wave and cheer the god on as he leaves the kingdom. A few of the faster dolpins follow him up to the surface and swin along the side of the chariot till the mares pull up and off into the sky. <br>
<br>
The islands and land masses spread out from below them and the sea god watches with great anticipation for his journey growing in his chest. No sooner did this anticipation come then when the mares smoothly pull into the stables at Olympus. Poseidon unpacks and leaves the mares some ambrosia. <br>
<br>
The home of the gods is bright and beautiful and Poseidon is pleased when upon arriving at the hall he see the tables set with silk cloths over which golden goblets, plates, pitchers and utensils are set neatly. There are 5 rectangular tables with 6 chairs apiece. One of the best choruses in all of Greece are there chatting with there instruments ready to be heard. <br>
<br>
Across the hall the sea god sees the man he is looking for and walks over to him. They speak for a little while about other things and a few immortals start arriving. as Poseidon sees this he motions to the chorus and they began to play out their gay melodies. Both Poseidon and his acquantance greet the others and the feast has begun! <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cybercomm.net/~grandpa/euterpe.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/6/02 11:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jonathonart.com/LotusMaiden1/dark1s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Departure of Hecate; Goddess of Sorcery</span><hr size=1> from down in Tartarus Hecate dresses in a sleek silk gown hued in a deep purple and her invitation in hand (assuming she got one)<br>
she departs passing through varrious chamber to her charroit.<br>
looking around she spots her dragons  tied to the wall; grabbing the best looking pair she hitches them to her charriot and in her right hand appears a mirror<br>
after a few moments of gazeing she winks and "poof" the mirror was gone<br>
slowly she mounts the charriot making sure her gown didnt get caught and in a burst of speed the dragons were off pulling her up as the earth tore open in front of her and seemlessly shut behind. She had thought to wait and see if her Persphone had wanted to catch a ride with her but at that moment anticipation had taken her captive.<br>
out of the earth she tore through the sky leaveing a trail of dust behind.<br>
shortly though she arrived at the stables and after unhitching her team she stroled through the hallways into the very hall where the feast was to be held. <p><a Target="_top"
