<br>
He stepped off the path and into the woods, shrugging off the cloak that concealed his broad frame.  He smiled, then in a blink of the eye he was gone.<br>
<br>
Lightning and thunder crashed throughout Olympus as if to say in the booming voice of Zeus, &quot;Honey, I'm home!&quot;  He appeared close to the banquet table and smiled broadly.  &quot;What a very pleasant surprise!&quot;  He quickly moved to embrace his wife, planting a kiss on her cheek.  He greeted both Hekate and Poseidon with equal vibrance, blessing them both with his touch and his smile.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goddessathena>Goddess Athena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/16/02 1:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Athena's Pressence</span><hr size=1> Once Zeus came into feeling distance of Olympus, Athena appeared in her golden entrance.<br>
She gave a nod to Hera and then smiled seeing her Father.<br>
Her bright green eyes glimmered in the torch light that lit near the table. She smiled brightly and bowed her head in great respect for her Father.<br>
<br>
&quot;I see that the King has once again returned. And in honored greetings too Father.&quot; She smiled. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessbia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Bia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.ptd.net/~crimson/paola.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/16/02 10:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theoi.com/image/T24.3Nike.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Athena's Pressence</span><hr size=1> Entering and looking around amazed by the splendor Posiedon had layed out for the feast.  Bia hoped she had been invited.<br>
<br>
Bia stood apart from the rest, the children of Styx and Pallas were always so very conspicuous.  Bia, like her brother and sisters, was a Golden Winged Goddess, dressed as always in robe and carrying the bow which was her constant companion.  One of the Gaudians of Zeus, she always needed to be prepared... (she thought to herself, she heard that had become a human motto too).<br>
<br>
She bowed towards Zeus and Hera and said &quot;Greetings to one and all!&quot;<br>
