<br>
The sea god strolls over to Hera giving simple greetings of 'Hi's and How's everything' to the immortals nearby. He steps into her presence and then grabbing her tosses her into the air and catches her as she fall back into his arms. 'Glad you could make it Hera.' He then sets her back on the ground smiling. 'You know I will be away for a while, kind of like Zeus(at the mention of Zeus' name the god himself arrives on Olympus) when he takes those long leaves of absence.' Poseidon playful taps he on the shoulder, 'So what's new sister, let us catch up before I leave!'<br>
<br>
At that moment that Poseidon finishes his statement Zeus steps in and plants a kiss on Hera's cheek. The god looks on at his brother and he grins, 'I've not seen your wandering behind in many moons.' he jokes. They clasp hands and shake them. 'It's good that the family is reunited again for a celebration of departure. So what is new with you as well my brother, come speak up I've not seen you and a long time.'<br>
<br>
The clamour of the feast escalates and the music plays dimly in the background. The food is being served and passed out among the guests who are already taking their fill of the potent drinks here.<br>
