<br>
As one of her children appeared, Hera smiled. But, then it was Eris who quickly walked over and began to flirt with her uncle, Poseidon.  Hera was unsure of these two possible part time lovers.  Any two gods paired together  could mean anything from war, treachory, or just too much drama for that matter.  Hera raised one brow over a pale icy orb as she gazed at the God of the Seas.  "And were my brother shall you be departing to...and how long?" <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uzeuskingofthegods.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeus King of the Gods</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/16/02 8:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Welcome one, welcome all!</span><hr size=1> Zeus' eyes dance with the lively music.  It is clear that the time away from Olympus has done the King of the Gods a world of good.  He greets his brother Poseidon with a handshake and then a brotherly hug, &quot;Brother, yes, do tell.  Where will your journeys take you?&quot;  He can't hide the smirk as he nods to Bia, his ever constant companion.  He nods in greeting to Eris as well.  Though some would argue that her presence on Olympus was blasphemous, he knew that for everything there must be a balance.  There could be no good without the bad.  This was fair and just.  He absolutely beamed as his eyes settled upon his pride and joy, Athena.  &quot;Ahh, the goddess of wisdom and Athens, does get more beautiful as the seasons progress.&quot;  He hugged his favorite child in greeting.  She was his chosen one, the one who did spring from his forehead fully formed.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/17/02 3:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Welcome Eris</span><hr size=1> Poseidon grasps a golden goblet from a silver tray that a cupbearer is passing around and thanks the young fellow who scurries off to offer drinks to others in their small groups or larger congregations laughing and smiling with one another. Poseidon is pleased with what he sees and takes a sip of the nectar. At the moment he removes the goblet from his lips Eris grabs his torso and this causes him to almost jump in startlement. Poseidon almost spits out the nectar onto Hera but catches himself before that happens and a small drizzle of it falls from the corner of his mouth down his chin. With his forearm the God wipes at the moisture there and excepts a kiss from Eris with delight.<br>
<br>
&quot;Eris so glad you too can make it!&quot; She then whispers to him about a present and the god wonders at what it could be, hopefully something worthwhile he thinks. &quot;I can't wait to find out what it is.&quot; he says. His eyes turn back to Hera and Zeus again and he blushes a little while holding the goblet up, &quot;To prosperity.&quot; He then drinks from it again.<br>
<br>
The god decides to continue on with Hera and Zeus from where they left off looking back to Eris often enough while he speaks. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hera I hope my leaving is not cause for celebration.&quot; he laughs. &quot;I just hope everyone is come to enjoy themselves. I know how everyone here is so uptight.&quot;<br>
<br>
Both Zeus and Hera ask Poseidon the same question about his trip and he takes another sip from the golden goblet before continuing. &quot;Well I am going east where the sun rises, to a land in which people are offering me rites of sacrifice, you know how it goes. There are few men I actually can like these days.&quot;<br>
<br>
The god licks his lips and before he can continue Zeus breaks his speech by greeting Athena. Now Athena and Poseidon were not the best of buddies, but he could tolerate her at times. What man could not tolerate one of the most beautiful goddesses in Olympus? &quot;Ah Athena, Zeus' favorite, Aegis bearer, welcome home you modest goddess.&quot; Poseidon dares to give her a kiss, on the cheek that is, he knows how those serious virgins are. <br>
<br>
&quot;We were just talking about where I am soon headed, care to join?&quot; He then remembers about Hecate and looks around but cannot spot her. &quot;I wonder where Hecate is though, have any of you seen her? I sent for one of the cup-bearers to go fetch her a little while ago. I wonder what is keeping her.&quot; He turns back to his company and smiles.<br>
<br>
The sharp cracking of utensils on dishes and cups on cups as immortals taost, and deep throated laughter are all around. Poseidon curses himself for not getting the Muses to play. Oh well, even the gods make petty mistakes.<br>
 <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessgaiax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Gaiax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/17/02 4:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/infernooffire/images/gaia3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Earthy One....</span><hr size=1> Green and gold lights burst into the room, when the rays where gone..there she stood. Locks of red touched her back and shoulders, emerald orbs where interupted by a few rogue strands of fiery red hair. Her body was cloaked in a green flowing gown with a golden outline. Sitting upon her divine head was a crown of vines, twigns, and leaves...Mother Earth had arrived.<br>
<br>
Bare feet paded to Zeus and Hera, though she was a Goddess of the older generation, she still bowed before the King and Queen of Olympus. She took two steps back from them after bowing, and took an upright position.<br>
<br>
&quot;Greetings, How are the King and Queen of Olypmus fairing this day?&quot;<br>
