<br>
&quot;The daughter of the great Zeus fairs well as well can be Father.&quot; She smirked. She found it humorous that she and her Father boosted their egos more than anyone could. <br>
Her eyes turned then to her uncle as he dared to kiss the virgin Goddess after the things he had done to her in Zeus' absence. She gave a nod and narrowed her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well in hopes that you're journeys are LONG and prosperous uncle.&quot; She took a sip of a nearby chalice.<br>
Her eyes then turned to Zeus as he questioned her about Athens. She smirked lightly and spoke.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well Father, I am in the process of raising a young boy to one day rule Athens as King. It's only proper seeing he has Immortal blood in his veins.&quot;<br>
<br>
She gave a look to Poseidon knowing he had such a hand in the attack, and then to Hera, who's son was her violator, and thent o Gaia knowing Gaia knew of Athena's son Erectheus, because it was from the Earth that the child sprung forth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cybercomm.net/~grandpa/euterpe.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/18/02 5:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=270.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jonathonart.com/LotusMaiden1/dark1s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feast of Departure</span><hr size=1> while standing in the hall Hecate is approached by a cupbearer speaking so swiftly and low she could hardly hear, his eyes catching glimpses of her every now and then as he anxiously stares at the floor.<br>
