She was uneasy.  The golden Dragon which hung around her neck moved, it's head turning this way and that.  It's eyes flashing a piercing red and smoke spouting from it's flaring nostrils.<br>
<br>
Bia's eyes burned like two suns.  There was a prescence, she could feel it,  the dragon felt it too.  Bia made a slow circut of the banqueting hall. She was seeking the perscence she could feel but not see and the voice she could hear albeit in the faintest of whispers.<br>
<br>
This was a place of feasting, a place of happiness.  Bia did not wish it to be less, but she had her duties to perform and anything which even remotely appeared a threat to Zeus and Hera would be sought out.<br>
<br>
&quot;If,&quot; she thought, sending a telepathic message, &quot;the owner of this voice would make himself known, then perhaps all would be well.  It was a good way also to seek the respect it sought.  It need only to assure her that all was well.&quot;  <br>
<br>
As she slowly walked around the room, the dragon became increasingly restless, it's eyes, like Bia's own, shone a warning to any who would tempt her wrath or pose a threat to her Lord and Lady here. <p>~ ~ Bia  Goddess of Force and Power: Warrior and Guardian of Zeus ~ ~

